      "writtenOn": "2019-02-28T20:35:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah, I think I\u0027m just realizing what I\u0027d forgotten: an \"active\" tryjob is not necessarily an unfinished job according to our DB; it\u0027s a job which we haven\u0027t marked as finished in Buildbucket.  I think I need to change this to look through ALL jobs and filter out those which have no BuildbucketLeaseKey.  Then I think I change the behavior for jobFinished back to what it was, ie. when I have an \"active\" try job which is finished, then I call jobFinished, as opposed to having the task scheduler call it.",
